text: Arizona's 29th Legislative District is one of 30 in the state, situated in central Maricopa County. As of 2018 there are 33 precincts in the district, with a total registered voter population of 81,424. ==Political representation== The district is represented for the 2018–2019 Legislative Session in the State Senate by Martín Quezada (D, Phoenix) and in the House of Representatives by Richard C. Andrade (D, Phoenix) and Cesar Chavez (D, Phoenix). ==References== Category:Maricopa County, Arizona Category:Arizona legislative districts
title: Arizona's 29th legislative district
